HEADWORD: hand-brake
<hw>hand"-brake`</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<def>a brake operated by hand, used to stop a vehicle or keep it
stationary; it usually operates by a mechanical linkage.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> handbrake, emergency, emergency brake, parking
brake.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

